## Redis Pub/Sub Flow

```
1. Finnhub WebSocket sends trade data for AAPL, MSFT, NVDA, GOOGL, AMZN, TSLA
2. finnhubService parses trades, updates latestPrices Map, emits 'priceUpdate' via EventEmitter
3. marketDataGateway listens to EventEmitter, PUBLISHES to Redis channel 'market:prices'
4. server.js Redis subscriber receives the message
5. server.js broadcasts to all Socket.io clients via io.emit('priceUpdate', data)
6. On new Socket.io connection, server emits 'priceSnapshot' with all cached prices
```

> [!NOTE]
> Redis Pub/Sub is used as the intermediary layer (not direct Finnhub → Socket.io) for future scalability. This allows multiple server instances to share market data through Redis, and enables future consumers (BullMQ workers, analytics pipelines) to subscribe to the same channel.

