## Socket.io Testing

```javascript
// In browser console or Node.js:
const { io } = require("socket.io-client");
const socket = io("http://localhost:5000");

socket.on("connect", () => console.log("Connected:", socket.id));
socket.on("priceSnapshot", (data) => console.log("Snapshot:", data));
socket.on("priceUpdate", (data) => console.log("Update:", data));
```

**Events:**
- `priceSnapshot` — emitted once on connection with all cached prices
- `priceUpdate` — emitted continuously with real-time price changes

