## Assumptions

1. Finnhub free tier API key is used (supports WebSocket + up to 50 symbols)
2. Paper trading only — $10,000 simulated cash, no real money
3. Existing users get portfolio auto-created on first `/portfolio` access (lazy init)
4. New users get portfolio auto-created on signup (fire-and-forget)
5. PortfolioSnapshot model is created but not yet populated (for future BullMQ job)
6. Market hours don't affect API availability — prices are cached from last received trade
7. No express-validator on InvestLab routes yet (basic validation in controllers)

